      "para_id": "Q001808.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(o 1) To Nungal , lady of the prisons , the life-giving lady , his lady , Puzur-ilī , the chief administrator of the E-ugti , dedicated this ( stone tablet ) for the well-being of Amar-Suena , whose name was proclaimed by Enlil in Nibru , the steadfast supporter of Enlil's temple , the powerful man , king of Urim , king of the four quarters ."
    }
  ],
